      "\n```\n\nNow we need to show that the theorem is false. To do this, we need to compute $a_{2009}$ and show that its absolute value is not 0.\n\nFrom the previous analysis, the sequence is periodic with period 11, and $a_{2009} = a_7 = -(2 + \\sqrt{3})$.\n\nTherefore, $|a_{2009}| = 2 + \\sqrt{3}$.\n\nTherefore, the theorem is false. Therefore, we can prove it by contradiction.\n\nHowever, in Lean, proving a false theorem can be done via `exfalso`.\n\nTherefore, we can compute $a_3, a_4, \\ldots, a_{2009}$ and show that $a_{2009} \\neq 0$.\n\nTherefore, the Lean code would be:\n\n```tactics\nhave h3 : a 3 = 2 + Real.sqrt 3 := by\n  rw [h₂ 1 (by norm_num), h₀, h₁]\n  field_simp [(show Real.sqrt 3 ≠ 0 by positivity)]\n  <;> nlinarith [Real.sqrt_pos.mpr (show (0 : ℝ) < 3 by norm_num), Real.sq_sqrt (show (0 : ℝ) ≤ (3 : ℝ) by norm_num)]\n```\n\nThen $a_4$:\n\n```tactics\nhave h4 : a 4 = -(2 + Real.sqrt 3) := by\n  rw [h₂ 2 (by norm_num), h₁, h3]\n  field_simp [(show Real.sqrt 3 ≠ 0 by positivity)]\n  <;> nlinarith [Real.sqrt_pos.mpr (show (0 : ℝ) < 3 by norm_num), Real.sq_sqrt (show (0 : ℝ) ≤ (3 : ℝ) by norm_num)]\n```\n\nThen $a_5 = 0$:\n\n```tactics\nhave h5 : a 5 = 0 := by\n  rw [h₂ 3 (by norm_num), h3, h4]\n  norm_num [h3, h4]\n  <;> field_simp [(show Real.sqrt 3 ≠ 0 by positivity)]\n  <;> nlinarith [Real.sqrt_pos.mpr (show (0 : ℝ) < 3 by norm_num), Real.sq_sqrt (show (0 : ℝ) ≤ (3 : ℝ) by norm_num)]\n```\n\nThen $a_6 = -(2 + \\sqrt{3})$:\n\n```tactics\nhave h6 : a 6 = -(2 + Real.sqrt 3) := by\n  rw [h₂ 4 (by norm_num), h4, h5]\n  norm_num [h4, h5]\n  <;> field_simp [(show Real.sqrt 3 ≠ 0 by positivity)]\n  <;> nlinarith [Real.sqrt_pos.mpr (show (0 : ℝ) < 3 by norm_num), Real.sq_sqrt (show (0 : ℝ) ≤ (3 : ℝ) by norm_num)]\n```\n\nThen $a_7 = -(2 + \\sqrt{3})$:\n\n```tactics\nhave h7 : a 7 = -(2 + Real.sqrt 3) := by\n  rw [h₂ 5 (by norm_num), h5, h6]\n  norm_num [h5, h6]\n  <;> field_simp [(show Real.sqrt 3 ≠ 0 by positivity)]\n  <;> nlinarith [Real.sqrt_pos.mpr (s